# Search Pipeline Stabilization Implementation Plan

We will fix the unused GraphQL variables causing 400 Bad Request errors on AniList search, and strip unstable search filters causing Jikan/MAL database timeouts (504).

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend API Client

#### [MODIFY] [AniListAdapter.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/api/AniListAdapter.ts)
- Dynamically build the GraphQL query signature to include `$genres` only when a genre filter is actually active. This prevents the `Variable "$genres" is never used` API error.

---

### Backend Proxy

#### [MODIFY] [JikanProvider.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/providers/JikanProvider.ts)
- Strip `score` and `rank` sorting from the `order_by` parameters in [cleanParams](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/providers/JikanProvider.ts#13-25). In Jikan/MyAnimeList, sorting search queries by these fields triggers unindexed slow database operations that result in a 504 Gateway Timeout. Removing them allows results to fall back on relevance-based sorting, returning responses instantly.

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Manual Verification
- Compile and run backend on port 5000.
- Verify search query `q=Naruto&orderBy=score&sort=desc` does not return a 500/504 error on backend.
- Using the browser subagent, verify the search page loads results successfully without any frontend console errors.
